# Forge & Table — E-commerce Frontend

A single-file React storefront for a kitchen knife and cookware shop, with a working cart, category filters, and an INR-based catalog.

## Features

- Hero section with a technical line-drawing illustration and spec callouts
- Category filtering (All / Knives / Cookware / Care) via top nav and in-page tabs
- Product catalog with 11 items, each with material, spec, and price
- Custom hand-drawn line icons per product (no external images)
- Slide-in cart drawer with quantity controls, subtotal, and checkout flow
- Toast notification on "Add to cart"
- Prices displayed in INR with Indian-style comma formatting
- Fully self-contained state management using React hooks (no backend required)

## Tech Stack

- React (functional components, hooks: useState, useMemo, useRef, useEffect)
- lucide-react for icons
- Inline CSS (via style tag) for full custom design control
- Google Fonts: Fraunces (display), IBM Plex Sans (body), IBM Plex Mono (specs/UI)

## File Structure
ForgeAndTable.jsx    - Single-file component containing all logic, styles, and markup

## How to Run

1. Create a new React project (or use an existing one):
npx create-react-app forge-and-table
cd forge-and-table
2. Install the icon library:
npm install lucide-react
3. Replace the contents of `src/App.js` with `ForgeAndTable.jsx`, or import it as a component:
import ForgeAndTable from "./ForgeAndTable";
export default function App() {
return <ForgeAndTable />;
}
4. Start the dev server:
npm start

## Customization Notes

- Product data lives in the `PRODUCTS` array near the top of the file. Add, remove, or edit entries here (id, name, category, icon type, material, spec, price, description).
- Categories are controlled by the `CATEGORIES` array — add a new category name here and tag matching products with it.
- Colors, fonts, and spacing are defined as CSS variables inside the `style` tag (`--ink`, `--paper`, `--steel`, `--ember`, etc.) — change these to re-theme the whole site.
- Icons are simple inline SVGs in the `ToolIcon` component — add a new case here for a new product type.

## Known Limitations

- No backend integration — cart and checkout are simulated in local state and reset on page refresh
- No payment gateway — "Place order" only shows a confirmation screen
- No product detail page — all product info is shown on the catalog card
- No persistent storage — cart contents are not saved between sessions

## Possible Next Steps

- Connect to a real backend or headless commerce API
- Add a product detail view/modal
- Integrate a payment gateway (Razorpay, Stripe, etc.)
- Add persistent cart storage
- Add search functionality
